text.tspan: Hold one or more note buttons
and hit up or down trigger.
Will play until you release note button
While playing any note you can play a hammer-on
by pressing any note closer to the body of the guitar
while holding a lower note. This note will play as soon
as you press the note button and does not require a trigger,
like a hammer-on on a guitar string.
You can also play a note, and release the note-button while
holding down a note further away from the body. This will
play the lower note without an additional trigger.
Hold the note buttons you want to tune,
press Select and Up/Down Trigger to tune
Each note can have different modes:
Hold notes, hold Select and press
Press Start to cycle through the modes
Press d-pad up/down to change the range
You can save Tremolo mode and range, as well
as selected notes and note modes to one of the 16
Press d-pad middle button, hold the first 4 buttons
(green, red, yellow, blue) to input a binary number,
release the d-pad middle button to save. Be careful
Hold d-pad middle button and hit trigger up/down, LEDs
display the current channel in binary.
